        <body>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-1">
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2097">
                            Simeon the mountaineer 
                        </persName>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/saint"/>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">229</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">229</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>
           <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-2">
               <listPerson>
                   <person>
                       <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2097"/>
                       <sex value="M">
                           <note type="desc">Simeon was male.</note>
                       </sex>
                   </person>
               </listPerson>
               <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">229</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">229</citedRange></bibl>
           </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-3">
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2097"/>
                        <occupation ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/anchorite">
                            <note type="desc">Simeon was an anchorite.</note>
                        </occupation>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">229</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">229</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-4">
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2097"/>
                        <state type="sanctity" ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/saint">
                            <note type="desc">Simeon was a saint.</note>
                        </state>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">229</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">229</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>
         <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-5">
             <listEvent>
                 <event>
                     <desc>
                         Simeon lived in the mountains like the wild beasts.
                     </desc>
                     <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/hermit"/>
                 </event>
             </listEvent>
             <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">229</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">229</citedRange></bibl>
         </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-6">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            Simeon would preach while in a state of ecstatic contemplation
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/ecstatic contemplation"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">229-231</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">229-231</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-7">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            Simeon came upon a settlement in 
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2864">
                                'bdhyr
                            </placeName>
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/settlement"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">232</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">232</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-8">
             <listPerson>
                 <personGrp>
                     <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/xxxx"><!-- URI needed for the Shepherds of Bdhyr -->
                         The shepherds who were addressed by
                         <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2097">
                             Simeon the mountaineer 
                         </persName>
                     </persName>
                 </personGrp>
             </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">232-233</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">232-233</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>  
        <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-9">
            <listPerson>
                <personGrp>
                    <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/xxxx"/><!-- URI needed for the Shepherds of Bdhyr -->
                    <residence>
                        <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2864"/>
                        <note type="desc">
                            These shepherds lived in 
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2864">
                            'bdhyr on the Euphrates
                            </placeName> 
                        </note>
                    </residence>
                </personGrp>
            </listPerson>
            <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">232-233</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">232-233</citedRange></bibl>
        </div> 
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-10">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            Simeon questioned the shepherds about their faith and Christian practices, only to learn that they had neglected their faith.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/religious practices"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">232-235</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">232-235</citedRange></bibl>
            </div> 
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-11">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            Simeon resolved to stay with the shepherds of 'bdhr and teach them how to worship God as Christians
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/religious practices"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">236</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">236</citedRange></bibl>
            </div> 
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-12">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            Simeon, in his wanderings, came upon a village in
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2823">
                                M'brn' and found their church abandoned and their faith neglected
                            </placeName>
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/religious practices"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">236</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">236</citedRange></bibl>
            </div> 
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-13">
            <listPerson>
                <personGrp>
                    <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/xxxx"><!-- URI needed for the men of M'rbn' -->
                        Some men from the village on the frontier of M'brn' 
                    </persName>
                </personGrp>
            </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">236</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">236</citedRange></bibl>
            </div> 
        <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-14">
            <listPerson>
                <personGrp>
                    <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/xxxx"/><!-- URI needed for the men of M'rbn' -->
                    <residence>
                        <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2823"/>
                        <note type="desc">
                            These men lived in M'brn'.
                        </note>
                    </residence>
                </personGrp>
            </listPerson>
            <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">236</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">236</citedRange></bibl>
        </div> 
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-15">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            John decided to take up residence in the abandoned church in 
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2823">
                                M'brn'
                            </placeName>
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/residence"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">237</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">237</citedRange></bibl>
            </div> 
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-16">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            John asked the people of the hamlet to gather around him so that he could proselytize and admonish them for neglecting their faith
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/proselytize"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">237-241</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">237-241</citedRange></bibl>
            </div> 
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-17">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            John made the oblation and communicated with the people of 
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2823">
                                M'brn'
                            </placeName>
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/communion"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">241</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">241</citedRange></bibl>
            </div> 
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-18">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            John called all of the children to him, divided them into two groups: the first was shut away in a room and the children in the second group, consisting of eighteen boys and twelve girls, were initiated into the clerical state by being tonsured.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/clerical initiation"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">243</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">243</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-19">
            <listPerson>
                <personGrp>
                    <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/xxxx"><!-- URI needed for the children of M'rbn' -->
                        The little children of M'rbn', all of whom were blessed and 30 of whom were tonsured by
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2097">
                            Simeon the mountaineer 
                        </persName>
                    </persName>
                </personGrp>
            </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">242-243</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">242-243</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-20">
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/xxxx"><!-- URI needed for the man who assisted Simeon tonsure the children -->
                            A man who assisted in tonsuring the children marked by
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2097">
                                Simeon the mountaineer 
                            </persName>
                        </persName>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/disciple"/><!-- Add the correct keyword -->
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">242-243</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">242-243</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>
        <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-21">
            <listPerson>
                <person>
                    <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/xxxx"/><!-- URI needed for the man who assisted Simeon tonsure the children -->
                    <sex value="M">
                        <note type="desc">This man was male.</note>
                    </sex>
                </person>
            </listPerson>
            <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">242-243</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">242-243</citedRange></bibl>
        </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-22"><!-- URI needed for the man who assisted Simeon tonsure the children -->
                <listRelation>
                    <relation ana="personal" name="snap:AllianceWith" mutual="http://syriaca.org/person/2097 http://syriaca.org/person/xxxx"/>
                </listRelation>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">242-243</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">242-243</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-23">
                <listRelation>
                    <relation ana="clerical" name="syriaca:Ordination" active="http://syriaca.org/person/2097" passive="xxx"/><!-- 1) Oxygen would not validate "ordained" 2) URI needed for the children who were tonsured so that they could be ordained by Simeon -->
                </listRelation>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">242-243</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">242-243</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-24">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            The parents at first opposed then accepted the tonsuring of their children.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/clerical initiation"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">243-244</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">243-244</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-25">
            <listPerson>
                <personGrp>
                    <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/xxxx"><!-- URI needed for the parents of the children blessed and tonsured by Simeon -->
                        The parents of the children blessed and tonsured by
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2097">
                            Simeon the mountaineer 
                        </persName>
                    </persName>
                </personGrp>
            </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">243-244</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">243-244</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>
         <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-26">
             <listRelation>
                 <relation ana="family" name="snap:ParentOf" active="http://syriaca.org/person/xxxx" passive="http://syriaca.org/person/xxxx"/><!-- URIs needed for the children tonsured by Simeon and their parents -->
             </listRelation>
             <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">242-244</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">242-244</citedRange></bibl>
         </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-27">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            Two of the tonsured children were taken away by parents who disapproved of Simeon's actions and were struck down with illness and died.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/death"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">244-245</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">244-245</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-28">
             <listPerson>
                 <personGrp>
                     <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/xxxx"><!-- URI needed for the two dead children whose parents who opposed Simeon -->
                         The two dead children whose parents opposed 
                         <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2097">
                             Simeon the mountaineer 
                         </persName>
                     </persName>
                 </personGrp>
             </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">244-245</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">244-245</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>
        <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-29">
            <listEvent>
                <event>
                    <desc>
                        Simeon received no further opposition, so that he continued to select and tonsure children, and within four or five years his church flourished.
                    </desc>
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/religious practices"/>
                </event>
            </listEvent>
            <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">246</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">246</citedRange></bibl>
        </div>
        <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/808-30">
            <listEvent>
                <event>
                    <desc>
                        Over the next twenty-six years John preached, gave blessings, and established himself as a spiritual teacher as the church he established flourished.
                    </desc>
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/religious practices"/>
                </event>
            </listEvent>
            <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/808"/><citedRange unit="pp">246-247</citedRange></bibl><bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange unit="pp">246-247</citedRange></bibl>
        </div>
        </body>
